  "body": "\r\nRelated: https://github.com/chakra-ui/chakra-ui/pull/10298\r\n\r\n## 📝 Description\r\n\r\nThis PR builds on the recently merged **Component Explorer** feature by updating component docs to include explorers where anatomies exist.\r\nIt also improves the explorer sidebar logic for more accurate part highlighting and cleaner presentation.\r\n\r\n## ⛳️ Current behavior (updates)\r\n\r\n* Only a subset of components currently has an Explorer.\r\n* Normalization of component names is limited, causing mismatches for some anatomy parts.\r\n* Element highlighting relies on fewer selectors and can miss edge cases.\r\n* Visual styles for borders and indicators are less consistent.\r\n\r\n## 🚀 New behavior\r\n\r\n* Explorers are now added to more component docs (limited to components with anatomies).\r\n* Example demos are extended to show all anatomy parts for clarity.\r\n* Improved `normalizeComponentName` ensures accurate sidebar → preview matching.\r\n* Broader selector support (`data-scope`, `chakra-*`, and bare part attributes) makes highlighting more robust.\r\n* Cleaner, simplified styles for borders, radius, and hover/active states.\r\n\r\n## 💣 Is this a breaking change (Yes/No):\r\n\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n## 📝 Additional Information\r\n\r\n* This is a **docs improvement only**.\r\n* Purpose: wrap up the Component Explorer task by extending coverage and refining the sidebar logic.",
